WEBVTT

1
00:00:32.125 --> 00:00:35.250
[♪ Theme music playing]

2
00:00:35.791 --> 00:00:37.208
[warlord] I think we can all agree

3
00:00:37.291 --> 00:00:39.166
that things were better under the Empire.

4
00:00:40.041 --> 00:00:43.250
Fortunately. I am still here to protect you.

5
00:00:44.250 --> 00:00:46.916
Your communities can thrive under my protection.

6
00:00:48.125 --> 00:00:50.083
You are the lucky few.

7
00:00:51.125 --> 00:00:53.458
But that which I provide is expensive.

8
00:00:54.500 --> 00:00:56.750
And now I must maintain all of it

9
00:00:56.833 --> 00:00:58.458
without the Empire's support

10
00:00:58.541 --> 00:01:00.791
until the galaxy realizes what they've lost

11
00:01:01.541 --> 00:01:03.041
and demand our return.

12
00:01:04.375 --> 00:01:06.625
Long live the Empire.

13
00:01:09.250 --> 00:01:11.500
[all] Long live the Empire.

14
00:01:13.416 --> 00:01:14.416
Good.

15
00:01:15.458 --> 00:01:16.750
Now for the bad news.

16
00:01:18.791 --> 00:01:20.666
I am raising your tribute.

17
00:01:20.750 --> 00:01:22.000
[gasps]

18
00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:24.791
But... [stammers]

19
00:01:24.875 --> 00:01:28.541
But. Your Excellency. we are operating at a loss.

20
00:01:30.333 --> 00:01:33.416
The trade routes are plagued with pirates and thieves.

21
00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:34.625
ready to attack at...

22
00:01:34.708 --> 00:01:36.083
[♪ theme music stops]

23
00:01:38.791 --> 00:01:41.041
Are you saying that my protection is lacking?

24
00:01:41.833 --> 00:01:43.916
No. Your Excellency.

25
00:01:45.666 --> 00:01:47.875
I-I am saying that. uh...

26
00:01:47.958 --> 00:01:49.291
[spectator gasps]

27
00:01:52.375 --> 00:01:55.250
Perhaps you should all go back to your townships

28
00:01:56.041 --> 00:01:57.750
and focus on solutions.

29
00:01:58.875 --> 00:02:00.291
not excuses.

30
00:02:02.291 --> 00:02:03.625
Does that sound reasonable?

31
00:02:05.625 --> 00:02:07.083
[alarm blaring]

32
00:02:07.166 --> 00:02:09.125
[static on comms]

33
00:02:09.208 --> 00:02:11.083
[snowtrooper 1] Sounds like a perimeter alarm.

34
00:02:11.166 --> 00:02:13.000
- I'll confirm.
- [blaster fires]

35
00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:17.750
- I've lost contact.
- Go check it.

36
00:02:17.833 --> 00:02:20.250
[alarm blaring continues]

37
00:02:20.791 --> 00:02:22.392
[warlord] There's nothing to worry about.

38
00:02:22.416 --> 00:02:24.666
- I'll send for reinforcements.
- [button clicks]

39
00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:30.920
[warlord] I will require a revenue projection...

40
00:02:30.958 --> 00:02:33.208
- [siren wails]
- [alarm blaring]

41
00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:39.750
- [whipcord launches]
- [grunts]

42
00:02:39.833 --> 00:02:41.333
[blaster firing]

43
00:02:47.083 --> 00:02:48.875
[blaster firing]

44
00:02:53.625 --> 00:02:55.726
[snowtrooper 2 over comms] <i>We need backup. On the double!</i>

45
00:02:55.750 --> 00:02:56.750
[snowtrooper 3] Code Red.

46
00:03:04.041 --> 00:03:05.125
Lay down cover fire.

47
00:03:07.416 --> 00:03:08.666
[snowtrooper 3] Take up arms!

48
00:03:10.375 --> 00:03:11.750
[button clicking rapidly]

49
00:03:11.833 --> 00:03:13.375
[♪ Tense music plays]

50
00:03:15.250 --> 00:03:16.333
[spectator gasps]

51
00:03:22.625 --> 00:03:24.416
Long live the Empire!

52
00:03:44.583 --> 00:03:47.250
[device beeping]

53
00:03:49.166 --> 00:03:50.250
[all gasp]

54
00:03:57.750 --> 00:03:59.708
[♪ Triumphant music plays]

55
00:03:59.791 --> 00:04:02.291
[whirring]

56
00:04:13.041 --> 00:04:14.875
[♪ Gentle music plays]

57
00:04:17.125 --> 00:04:18.458
[exclaims]

58
00:04:18.541 --> 00:04:20.166
[mechanical stomping]

59
00:04:32.333 --> 00:04:35.250
[machine whirring. clangs]

60
00:04:35.333 --> 00:04:38.250
[device beeping]

61
00:04:48.291 --> 00:04:50.833
[beeping accelerates]

62
00:05:07.791 --> 00:05:10.000
What are you waiting for? Hop on.

63
00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:27.666
Hang on.

64
00:05:27.750 --> 00:05:28.833
[screams]

65
00:05:51.416 --> 00:05:52.416
[artillery firing]

66
00:05:54.291 --> 00:05:55.291
Did we get him?

67
00:05:55.375 --> 00:05:56.815
[pilot 1] Not yet. sir. But we will.

68
00:06:05.041 --> 00:06:07.708
- We missed him! He's under us.
- [commander] <i>We have him.</i>

69
00:06:07.791 --> 00:06:08.791
<i>Fire.</i>

70
00:06:19.458 --> 00:06:20.875
[The Mandalorian grunting]

71
00:06:26.916 --> 00:06:27.916
[grunts]

72
00:06:29.791 --> 00:06:31.125
[beeping]

73
00:06:53.833 --> 00:06:55.916
<i>What's going on? Give me a status report.</i>

74
00:06:56.000 --> 00:06:57.541
<i>Has the target been eliminated?</i>

75
00:06:57.625 --> 00:06:59.833
- [pilot 2] We've lost contact.
- Walker Three is gone.

76
00:07:00.458 --> 00:07:02.666
- [warlord] <i>Send everybody!</i>
- Understood.

77
00:07:02.750 --> 00:07:03.958
Prepare to engage!

78
00:07:04.041 --> 00:07:06.625
[alarm blaring]

79
00:07:12.833 --> 00:07:13.916
Get ready. Weapons up.

80
00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:15.500
Full barrel. Now. let's go.

81
00:07:20.083 --> 00:07:21.583
[snow troopers grunting]

82
00:07:23.541 --> 00:07:25.458
[groaning]

83
00:07:26.083 --> 00:07:28.208
[screaming]

84
00:07:30.291 --> 00:07:32.583
[grunting. screaming]

85
00:07:45.458 --> 00:07:46.458
[exclaims]

86
00:07:50.541 --> 00:07:52.208
[warlord] <i>Give me a status update.</i>

87
00:07:52.291 --> 00:07:54.541
<i>Did you see him? Have you located him?</i>

88
00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:57.208
<i>Did you get The Mandalorian?</i>

89
00:07:57.291 --> 00:07:59.375
[metal clangs]

90
00:07:59.458 --> 00:08:00.458
Something's up there.

91
00:08:02.625 --> 00:08:03.958
He's on the roof!

92
00:08:04.625 --> 00:08:05.625
<i>Can you see him?</i>

93
00:08:06.291 --> 00:08:07.291
<i>Take him out!</i>

94
00:08:07.375 --> 00:08:08.375
Get up there.

95
00:08:09.166 --> 00:08:10.291
But we're pilots.

96
00:08:10.375 --> 00:08:13.083
- Go now! Do it!
- Yes. sir. On our way.

97
00:08:13.166 --> 00:08:14.500
Get up there.

98
00:08:15.666 --> 00:08:16.706
[warlord] Set the charges.

99
00:08:16.750 --> 00:08:18.166
- Prepare for exfil.
- Sir.

100
00:08:18.250 --> 00:08:21.625
<i>He's breaching the hatch. He's breaching the hatch!</i>

101
00:08:27.583 --> 00:08:29.083
[screams]

102
00:08:35.833 --> 00:08:37.333
[grunts]

103
00:08:39.375 --> 00:08:40.375
Autopilot.

104
00:08:44.458 --> 00:08:45.541
[blaster firing]

105
00:08:51.208 --> 00:08:53.208
[rapid beeping]

106
00:08:55.208 --> 00:08:57.333
[♪ Tense music plays]

107
00:09:07.583 --> 00:09:09.083
[babbling frantically]

108
00:09:09.166 --> 00:09:10.666
[rapid beeping continues]

109
00:09:10.750 --> 00:09:11.916
[exclaims]

110
00:09:13.291 --> 00:09:15.208
I know. I know. I need to get the shot.

111
00:09:17.791 --> 00:09:18.916
[Grogu groans]

112
00:09:19.875 --> 00:09:21.250
[targeting system beeping]

113
00:09:24.708 --> 00:09:25.750
[screams]

114
00:09:38.333 --> 00:09:39.666
[ship engine approaching]

115
00:09:43.750 --> 00:09:45.208
[The Mandalorian grunts]

116
00:09:45.291 --> 00:09:47.958
You know. it's better if you bring 'em in alive.

117
00:09:55.041 --> 00:09:56.041
You okay?

118
00:09:57.083 --> 00:09:58.083
[sneezes]

119
00:09:58.666 --> 00:10:00.875
You see. you catch the bad guy

120
00:10:00.958 --> 00:10:03.333
and they tell us where the other bad guys are.

121
00:10:04.041 --> 00:10:05.791
Things went a little sideways.

122
00:10:09.291 --> 00:10:10.750
[engine accelerates]

123
00:10:22.416 --> 00:10:24.916
[♪ Theme music playing]

124
00:12:00.041 --> 00:12:01.375
[no audible dialogue]

125
00:12:06.208 --> 00:12:08.208
[♪ Theme music ends]

126
00:12:09.083 --> 00:12:12.166
[droid warbling]

127
00:12:26.666 --> 00:12:29.458
Good luck. You're gonna need it.

128
00:12:37.958 --> 00:12:40.625
Messy. Very messy.

129
00:12:41.916 --> 00:12:44.541
It was the best I could do under the circumstances.

130
00:12:45.541 --> 00:12:47.541
The problem is. we need information.

131
00:12:48.416 --> 00:12:50.309
Without it. we're never gonna get to the bottom of

132
00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:52.166
what the Empire's up to.

133
00:12:52.250 --> 00:12:53.250
Just give me time.

134
00:12:53.333 --> 00:12:55.833
I'll take out every bad guy in your deck of cards.

135
00:12:55.916 --> 00:12:57.458
This isn't about revenge.

136
00:12:57.958 --> 00:13:00.583
It's about preventing another war...

137
00:13:01.541 --> 00:13:02.541
[Grogu groans]

138
00:13:03.833 --> 00:13:06.500
And protecting everything the Rebellion fought for.

139
00:13:06.583 --> 00:13:08.791
Does that mean I'm not getting paid for this one?

140
00:13:10.583 --> 00:13:12.416
You're getting paid all right.

141
00:13:12.500 --> 00:13:13.500
Come with me.

142
00:13:22.833 --> 00:13:24.041
[The Mandalorian] Impressive.

143
00:13:24.125 --> 00:13:25.458
Where did you get one of these?

144
00:13:26.166 --> 00:13:28.291
It was from a captured Imperial commandant

145
00:13:28.375 --> 00:13:30.625
who had a big collection of vintage vehicles.

146
00:13:31.125 --> 00:13:33.750
This one is stock. Perfectly restored.

147
00:13:34.416 --> 00:13:36.125
I took it out for a test spin.

148
00:13:36.708 --> 00:13:38.625
They did a nice job on the rebuild.

149
00:13:41.333 --> 00:13:43.101
[The Mandalorian] This is worth a lot more than

150
00:13:43.125 --> 00:13:44.625
the bounty on that Imp.

151
00:13:44.708 --> 00:13:47.333
Well. let's call it an advance on the next mission.

152
00:13:49.583 --> 00:13:50.708
What next mission?

153
00:13:51.375 --> 00:13:52.833
Commander Coin.

154
00:13:53.833 --> 00:13:55.333
Our missing Ace of Staves.

155
00:13:57.750 --> 00:13:59.416
No one knows what he looks like

156
00:13:59.500 --> 00:14:01.541
and most believe him to be dead.

157
00:14:02.250 --> 00:14:05.000
Not a lot to go on. What's the play?

158
00:14:05.083 --> 00:14:08.250
I want you to go to Nal Hutta and meet with the Hutts.

159
00:14:08.833 --> 00:14:10.791
They've agreed to lead us to him.

160
00:14:10.875 --> 00:14:11.875
What's in it for them?

161
00:14:12.500 --> 00:14:14.833
Their nephew's being held against his will

162
00:14:14.916 --> 00:14:17.416
by another crime syndicate on the Outer Rim.

163
00:14:17.500 --> 00:14:18.708
and they need a professional

164
00:14:18.791 --> 00:14:20.375
to get him out quickly and quietly.

165
00:14:20.458 --> 00:14:21.458
Where is he?

166
00:14:21.958 --> 00:14:23.416
They'll only tell you in person.

167
00:14:24.250 --> 00:14:25.250
You got a name?

168
00:14:25.958 --> 00:14:27.583
His name is Rotta the Hutt.

169
00:14:27.666 --> 00:14:31.083
The only surviving heir of crime lord Jabba the Hutt.

170
00:14:31.666 --> 00:14:32.916
You ever cross his path?

171
00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:34.625
I tried not to.

172
00:14:35.833 --> 00:14:36.833
So...

173
00:14:37.708 --> 00:14:38.833
do we have a deal?

174
00:14:38.916 --> 00:14:41.291
I only hunt down Imperial war criminals.

175
00:14:41.375 --> 00:14:44.833
I don't work for gangsters anymore. especially the Hutts.

176
00:14:44.916 --> 00:14:47.416
That's right. you don't. You work for us.

177
00:14:47.500 --> 00:14:50.333
And right now. this is what we need you to do.

178
00:14:51.000 --> 00:14:53.958
You don't want the job. I got nothing for you.

179
00:15:05.750 --> 00:15:06.791
[Zeb] Come aboard.

180
00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:10.833
May as well have a look around.

181
00:15:15.791 --> 00:15:17.333
Let's go hear the Hutts out.

182
00:15:17.958 --> 00:15:19.958
I'll even let you fly this time.

183
00:15:20.500 --> 00:15:22.416
- I didn't say yes.
- [thudding]

184
00:15:22.500 --> 00:15:24.166
[Zeb] You didn't say no either.

185
00:15:24.250 --> 00:15:27.041
- [thudding]
- [giggling. panting]

186
00:15:42.875 --> 00:15:45.541
[♪ Theme music playing]

187
00:15:46.500 --> 00:15:48.666
She's stock. but she's clean.

188
00:15:56.083 --> 00:15:58.333
[engine whirring]

189
00:15:59.625 --> 00:16:01.125
[Grogu grunting]

190
00:16:04.041 --> 00:16:05.458
[mechanism powers up]

191
00:16:05.541 --> 00:16:07.291
- Hey.
- [babbling]

192
00:16:07.375 --> 00:16:08.583
Don't touch anything.

193
00:16:09.125 --> 00:16:10.458
Never touch the buttons.

194
00:16:14.583 --> 00:16:15.916
[groans]

195
00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:42.750
[♪ Triumphant theme music plays]

196
00:17:00.000 --> 00:17:01.458
[engine accelerates]

197
00:17:06.833 --> 00:17:09.458
[♪ Gentle theme music plays]

198
00:17:24.208 --> 00:17:26.500
[♪ Ominous music plays]

199
00:17:31.750 --> 00:17:33.333
[rapid beeping]

200
00:17:35.750 --> 00:17:37.458
[switches clicking]

201
00:17:54.125 --> 00:17:56.166
[robotic voice over comms] <i>Identify yourself.</i>

202
00:17:57.458 --> 00:17:59.916
<i>Razor Crest.</i> requesting clearance.

203
00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:02.000
I'm here by invitation of the Twins.

204
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:06.333
Easy on the sticks. They're expecting us.

205
00:18:07.041 --> 00:18:08.291
We should be fine.

206
00:18:10.708 --> 00:18:12.476
[robotic voice over comms] <i>Clearance granted.</i>

207
00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:13.875
<i>You are clear to approach.</i>

208
00:18:14.708 --> 00:18:16.750
They've got a lot of firepower here.

209
00:18:16.833 --> 00:18:19.958
Yeah. Looks like they hired the Droid Gotra.

210
00:18:20.041 --> 00:18:22.041
The Hutts take security seriously.

211
00:18:49.500 --> 00:18:51.500
[♪ Ominous music continues]

212
00:19:13.125 --> 00:19:15.017
The Hutts have been the head of criminal enterprises

213
00:19:15.041 --> 00:19:16.583
for thousands of years.

214
00:19:17.458 --> 00:19:19.058
- [speaks Huttese]
- [frantic chittering]

215
00:19:21.083 --> 00:19:23.043
[The Mandalorian] They use violence and treachery

216
00:19:23.125 --> 00:19:24.333
to maintain control.

217
00:19:26.083 --> 00:19:27.458
Be careful.

218
00:19:27.541 --> 00:19:32.125
We may be their guests. but we are not safe.

219
00:19:53.083 --> 00:19:54.333
[device beeps]

220
00:20:16.125 --> 00:20:19.375
[in Huttese] We finally meet the legendary Mandalorian.

221
00:20:20.583 --> 00:20:25.000
We are so glad you agreed to work for us.

222
00:20:25.583 --> 00:20:27.833
You will be very rich.

223
00:20:27.916 --> 00:20:29.458
[in English] I don't work for you.

224
00:20:29.541 --> 00:20:31.041
I work for the New Republic.

225
00:20:31.916 --> 00:20:33.000
I'm told you can lead us

226
00:20:33.083 --> 00:20:35.375
to the Imperial fugitive Commander Coin.

227
00:20:36.250 --> 00:20:38.500
[in Huttese] Of course. Mando.

228
00:20:38.583 --> 00:20:40.383
[in English] I understand your nephew. Rotta.

229
00:20:40.416 --> 00:20:41.708
has been kidnapped.

230
00:20:42.041 --> 00:20:45.083
[in Huttese] Yes. our poor nephew has been taken.

231
00:20:46.000 --> 00:20:48.625
He fell in with a bad crowd.

232
00:20:49.041 --> 00:20:51.708
We are heartbroken.

233
00:20:52.458 --> 00:20:55.208
[in English] Think of how you would feel

234
00:20:55.291 --> 00:20:58.375
if your little one went missing.

235
00:20:58.916 --> 00:20:59.916
[Grogu groans]

236
00:21:00.666 --> 00:21:02.166
What does he look like?

237
00:21:02.250 --> 00:21:03.458
Do you have an image?

238
00:21:03.750 --> 00:21:05.083
[in Huttese] Ah. yes.

239
00:21:05.583 --> 00:21:09.375
The only image we have is from long ago.

240
00:21:09.875 --> 00:21:11.291
[device humming]

241
00:21:13.875 --> 00:21:14.958
[Grogu babbles]

242
00:21:15.958 --> 00:21:19.666
He's had a growth spurt since then.

243
00:21:20.416 --> 00:21:24.000
[in English] Okay. I'll rescue your nephew.

244
00:21:24.083 --> 00:21:25.083
Where is he being held?

245
00:21:25.750 --> 00:21:30.666
[in Huttese] You will find him on the moon of Shakari.

246
00:21:31.250 --> 00:21:32.666
[in English] It shall be done.

247
00:21:44.875 --> 00:21:46.125
[engine accelerates]

248
00:21:52.166 --> 00:21:53.916
We're about to come out of hyperspace

249
00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:55.333
in the Shakari system.

250
00:21:55.958 --> 00:21:58.158
[through comms] <i>To state the obvious. you are operating</i>

251
00:21:58.208 --> 00:22:00.375
<i>outside the jurisdiction of the New Republic.</i>

252
00:22:01.500 --> 00:22:05.375
If things get messy. I can't call in an X-wing strike.

253
00:22:05.916 --> 00:22:07.791
I know the drill.

254
00:22:08.666 --> 00:22:12.291
Before going into harm's way. check your armor first.

255
00:22:12.375 --> 00:22:14.833
It's gotta fit snug so it doesn't slide.

256
00:22:14.916 --> 00:22:17.541
but not so tight that it restricts your movement.

257
00:22:18.250 --> 00:22:19.416
Got it?

258
00:22:19.500 --> 00:22:20.833
[babbles]

259
00:22:20.916 --> 00:22:22.416
- How's that feel?
- [coos]

260
00:22:28.166 --> 00:22:30.625
[♪ dramatic electronic music playing]

261
00:22:46.125 --> 00:22:47.916
All right. Zeb. drop us here.

262
00:23:16.083 --> 00:23:19.083
[♪ Dramatic electronic music continues]

263
00:23:42.416 --> 00:23:44.416
- [♪ Music fades]
- [Grogu grunts]

264
00:23:44.500 --> 00:23:45.500
Yes?

265
00:23:45.583 --> 00:23:47.383
I'll take a flat-meat fry for the little one.

266
00:23:47.416 --> 00:23:49.125
Got it. Okay. got it. got it.

267
00:23:49.208 --> 00:23:50.666
Flat-meat fry. huh?

268
00:23:53.208 --> 00:23:54.851
- Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah.
- [strains]

269
00:23:54.875 --> 00:23:57.916
[vendor mutters in Ardennian]

270
00:24:01.041 --> 00:24:02.333
[chuckles] Whoa.

271
00:24:02.416 --> 00:24:04.142
[in English] That's quite an impressive denomination.

272
00:24:04.166 --> 00:24:05.601
I'm not sure I've got change for that.

273
00:24:05.625 --> 00:24:07.017
[The Mandalorian] You can keep the change.

274
00:24:07.041 --> 00:24:08.666
I'm new to these parts.

275
00:24:08.750 --> 00:24:10.875
I can use some information.

276
00:24:10.958 --> 00:24:13.333
Yeah. for this price. I'll tell you whatever you want.

277
00:24:13.833 --> 00:24:15.250
I'm looking for a Hutt.

278
00:24:15.333 --> 00:24:17.833
Shh. Don't mention that name. Don't say that.

279
00:24:17.916 --> 00:24:19.392
What. are you trying to get us both killed?

280
00:24:19.416 --> 00:24:21.500
Here. Keep your credits. Food's on me.

281
00:24:22.041 --> 00:24:23.833
Go away. Thank you.

282
00:24:23.916 --> 00:24:26.500
Okay. never happened. Let's go. Nothing to see here.

283
00:24:26.583 --> 00:24:28.166
Damn Mandalorian. talking like that.

284
00:24:28.250 --> 00:24:30.500
Just out in the open. he talks like... What is this?

285
00:24:30.583 --> 00:24:33.250
No. no. no. No. no. no. no. I don't want your credits.

286
00:24:33.333 --> 00:24:34.809
'cause I didn't give you any information.

287
00:24:34.833 --> 00:24:36.250
His name is Rotta.

288
00:24:37.125 --> 00:24:38.125
Really?

289
00:24:38.208 --> 00:24:39.541
[laughing]

290
00:24:40.416 --> 00:24:41.666
Something funny?

291
00:24:41.750 --> 00:24:43.208
Yeah. yeah. Everybody... [chuckles]

292
00:24:43.291 --> 00:24:45.125
Everybody knows Rotta the Hutt.

293
00:24:45.208 --> 00:24:47.333
That guy's a monster. [Chuckles]

294
00:24:52.125 --> 00:24:54.750
[crowd cheering. whistling]

295
00:24:55.250 --> 00:24:56.750
[Rotta growling]

296
00:24:59.458 --> 00:25:01.041
[roaring]

297
00:25:01.708 --> 00:25:04.125
[both grunting]

298
00:25:05.666 --> 00:25:06.708
[crowd cheers]

299
00:25:22.916 --> 00:25:24.083
[strains]

300
00:25:29.750 --> 00:25:31.958
[roars]

301
00:25:33.583 --> 00:25:34.958
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta!

302
00:25:35.041 --> 00:25:37.208
He doesn't seem like a prisoner to me.

303
00:25:39.291 --> 00:25:41.091
- [pit announcer] ...Rotta!
- [crowd cheering]

304
00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:44.000
[crowd chanting]

305
00:25:44.791 --> 00:25:45.875
[roars]

306
00:26:05.208 --> 00:26:07.916
[mechanical buzzing]

307
00:26:15.791 --> 00:26:17.250
[The Mandalorian speaks Huttese]

308
00:26:21.208 --> 00:26:22.750
Are you here to kill me?

309
00:26:23.625 --> 00:26:25.333
[in English] I'm here to rescue you.

310
00:26:27.458 --> 00:26:29.833
What makes you think I need rescuing?

311
00:26:29.916 --> 00:26:31.791
Your aunt and uncle hired me to find you.

312
00:26:31.875 --> 00:26:32.916
[scoffs]

313
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:37.000
Yeah. I see. Well. thank you. but I don't require rescuing.

314
00:26:37.625 --> 00:26:40.041
Tomorrow's the last match in my contract and after that.

315
00:26:40.125 --> 00:26:41.833
my debt will be paid.

316
00:26:41.916 --> 00:26:43.583
I'll be a free agent. [Crunches]

317
00:26:45.125 --> 00:26:46.916
[exclaims excitedly]

318
00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:48.333
Paid to who?

319
00:26:48.416 --> 00:26:50.125
[whines]

320
00:26:51.166 --> 00:26:52.166
Who's he?

321
00:26:53.291 --> 00:26:55.125
- Don't stare.
- [babbles]

322
00:26:55.208 --> 00:26:57.166
It's okay. What's your name?

323
00:26:57.250 --> 00:26:59.208
- [exclaims]
- He doesn't talk.

324
00:26:59.291 --> 00:27:00.916
Who do you have to pay?

325
00:27:01.000 --> 00:27:02.375
Can I feed him?

326
00:27:02.458 --> 00:27:04.125
[whining]

327
00:27:06.375 --> 00:27:07.583
Sure.

328
00:27:07.666 --> 00:27:09.083
Who do you have to pay?

329
00:27:12.416 --> 00:27:14.791
[babbles. gulps]

330
00:27:14.875 --> 00:27:16.291
Lord Janu.

331
00:27:17.666 --> 00:27:19.250
I don't know the name.

332
00:27:19.333 --> 00:27:20.708
You should.

333
00:27:20.791 --> 00:27:23.541
He runs the Syndicate on all the moons of Shakari.

334
00:27:26.166 --> 00:27:27.583
He signed me to his stable.

335
00:27:27.666 --> 00:27:29.833
He bankrolled my board and training.

336
00:27:29.916 --> 00:27:31.791
He keeps you in a cage.

337
00:27:31.875 --> 00:27:33.000
He treats me well.

338
00:27:33.541 --> 00:27:36.333
And after tomorrow night. I'll be my own man.

339
00:27:36.416 --> 00:27:39.000
And with the following he got me as a promoter.

340
00:27:39.083 --> 00:27:41.166
not only will my debt be paid.

341
00:27:41.250 --> 00:27:42.750
but I'll be rich by the solstice.

342
00:27:42.833 --> 00:27:44.958
- [giggles]
- Grogu. heel!

343
00:27:47.750 --> 00:27:50.250
Don't worry. I'm not my father.

344
00:27:52.000 --> 00:27:53.541
[crunching]

345
00:27:55.708 --> 00:27:58.083
You know how hard it is to be your own man

346
00:27:58.166 --> 00:28:00.041
when your father is Jabba the Hutt?

347
00:28:05.666 --> 00:28:08.083
You see them cheering for me out there?

348
00:28:08.166 --> 00:28:09.166
For me.

349
00:28:09.916 --> 00:28:13.125
It's the first time I'm not living in his shadow.

350
00:28:13.208 --> 00:28:15.250
That's why I fight in the pits.

351
00:28:15.750 --> 00:28:19.041
They feared him. but they cheer for me.

352
00:28:20.833 --> 00:28:22.083
So. no...

353
00:28:22.791 --> 00:28:24.666
I don't need to be rescued.

354
00:28:25.333 --> 00:28:26.750
[mechanical buzzing resumes]

355
00:28:28.666 --> 00:28:30.416
Where can I find Lord Janu?

356
00:28:32.125 --> 00:28:34.000
Thank you. Closed for the night.

357
00:28:34.666 --> 00:28:36.541
[Grogu babbles]

358
00:28:38.833 --> 00:28:41.000
What the hell's he thinking? Damn Mandalorians.

359
00:28:41.083 --> 00:28:42.726
Mandalorians. they don't even come from here.

360
00:28:42.750 --> 00:28:44.333
He's going around. talking... [shouts]

361
00:28:45.583 --> 00:28:48.583
I just wanna know where I can find Lord Janu.

362
00:28:48.666 --> 00:28:51.916
Don't say that. Do not say that name.

363
00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:53.541
Stop saying it.

364
00:28:53.625 --> 00:28:55.750
I recommend you calm down.

365
00:28:56.291 --> 00:28:57.976
Just. please. please. don't kill me. Don't kill me.

366
00:28:58.000 --> 00:28:59.833
I've got... I've got 12 little ones at home.

367
00:28:59.916 --> 00:29:01.958
smaller than him. It's... They're smaller.

368
00:29:02.791 --> 00:29:04.750
[sighs] Yeah. it's just...

369
00:29:04.833 --> 00:29:07.208
[sighs] I pay him protection. okay?

370
00:29:07.291 --> 00:29:08.291
We all do.

371
00:29:08.375 --> 00:29:09.916
I barely make a living. to be honest.

372
00:29:10.000 --> 00:29:12.416
- But at least I'm alive.
- Who collects for him?

373
00:29:12.500 --> 00:29:14.166
I don't know. Different people come in.

374
00:29:14.250 --> 00:29:16.392
Sometimes they come here. sometimes I do a drop myself.

375
00:29:16.416 --> 00:29:17.958
- What do I know?
- Where?

376
00:29:18.041 --> 00:29:20.750
- Where what?
- Where do you do the drops?

377
00:29:20.833 --> 00:29:22.208
I don't... Some pla... Sometimes.

378
00:29:22.291 --> 00:29:24.208
I go down to... [stammers] ...different places.

379
00:29:24.291 --> 00:29:26.250
Usually... Sometimes I go to the salt bar

380
00:29:26.333 --> 00:29:28.125
under Korvin Station.

381
00:29:28.208 --> 00:29:30.166
And then there's other places too. You go to...

382
00:29:30.250 --> 00:29:31.916
You know. You know. I go around.

383
00:29:32.000 --> 00:29:33.000
[coin clinks]

384
00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:35.375
No. I don't want it. I don't want it.

385
00:29:35.458 --> 00:29:36.833
I didn't give you any information.

386
00:29:36.916 --> 00:29:38.916
- I was just talking.
- That's not for information.

387
00:29:39.208 --> 00:29:40.416
It's to cover his tab.

388
00:29:41.458 --> 00:29:43.250
[crunches]

389
00:29:59.500 --> 00:30:03.708
- [chittering. buzzing]
- [patrons chattering]

390
00:30:26.250 --> 00:30:27.750
I'm looking for Lord Janu.

391
00:30:28.333 --> 00:30:30.416
[chatter quiets]

392
00:30:32.375 --> 00:30:34.291
Maybe you made a mistake.

393
00:30:36.250 --> 00:30:38.916
Maybe you remember wrong and think you know me.

394
00:30:42.458 --> 00:30:44.666
Maybe you just walked through the wrong door.

395
00:30:46.000 --> 00:30:48.375
Well. I'm not here to buy salt.

396
00:30:49.166 --> 00:30:50.375
Salt?

397
00:30:51.208 --> 00:30:52.583
We don't sell salt.

398
00:30:53.500 --> 00:30:54.625
It's on the ration.

399
00:30:57.083 --> 00:30:59.083
How much for the shoulder candy?

400
00:30:59.166 --> 00:31:00.541
[Grogu groans]

401
00:31:00.625 --> 00:31:01.875
[chuckles]

402
00:31:01.958 --> 00:31:03.833
Would look real pretty in a cage.

403
00:31:04.916 --> 00:31:06.583
I'm here to see Lord Janu.

404
00:31:07.875 --> 00:31:09.958
I won't repeat myself again.

405
00:31:14.208 --> 00:31:15.208
[device buzzes]

406
00:31:19.708 --> 00:31:21.333
- [Grogu exclaims]
- [chittering]

407
00:31:21.416 --> 00:31:23.625
[grunting]

408
00:31:27.791 --> 00:31:29.125
- [grunts]
- [screeching]

409
00:31:41.083 --> 00:31:42.416
[groans]

410
00:31:44.583 --> 00:31:46.208
[grunting]

411
00:31:46.833 --> 00:31:47.833
[armor clangs]

412
00:31:48.750 --> 00:31:49.958
[shouts]

413
00:31:50.833 --> 00:31:52.250
[helmet clangs]

414
00:31:52.750 --> 00:31:53.750
[grunts]

415
00:31:53.833 --> 00:31:56.666
[The Mandalorian breathes heavily]

416
00:31:58.750 --> 00:32:01.041
It seems you've earned your salt today.

417
00:32:04.208 --> 00:32:05.250
I'm Janu.

418
00:32:06.333 --> 00:32:08.291
Come to the back and pick out a crystal.

419
00:32:08.791 --> 00:32:09.791
Hogsbreth.

420
00:32:11.625 --> 00:32:13.166
have the boys clean up.

421
00:32:14.458 --> 00:32:16.583
Make sure I don't lose any pets.

422
00:32:17.458 --> 00:32:20.208
[pets fluttering. chittering]

423
00:32:29.708 --> 00:32:31.541
[chittering]

424
00:32:35.250 --> 00:32:36.250
Here.

425
00:32:37.000 --> 00:32:38.166
Choose one.

426
00:32:38.250 --> 00:32:40.875
Salt is of no value to me where I'm from.

427
00:32:40.958 --> 00:32:42.958
But here it's worth a small fortune.

428
00:32:43.041 --> 00:32:46.291
because it's rationed by the politicians.

429
00:32:47.000 --> 00:32:48.500
Which makes it rare.

430
00:32:49.958 --> 00:32:51.625
As are you. Mandalorian.

431
00:32:53.208 --> 00:32:55.291
Have you ever considered fighting in the pits?

432
00:32:55.375 --> 00:32:57.375
I try to avoid violence.

433
00:32:58.791 --> 00:33:00.000
'Course you do.

434
00:33:01.000 --> 00:33:02.208
I do as well.

435
00:33:04.041 --> 00:33:05.708
So what brings you to this establishment

436
00:33:05.791 --> 00:33:07.375
if you're not in the market for salt?

437
00:33:07.458 --> 00:33:10.416
I wanna buy out the contract on a fighter from your stable.

438
00:33:11.041 --> 00:33:13.708
Perhaps you would consider joining my stable instead?

439
00:33:19.875 --> 00:33:22.416
This buys a lot of salt where I'm from.

440
00:33:22.500 --> 00:33:23.666
I am offering you this

441
00:33:23.750 --> 00:33:26.541
in exchange for the fighting contract on Rotta the Hutt.

442
00:33:26.625 --> 00:33:28.666
My dear boy. there's no price high enough

443
00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:30.875
to buy him out of his last fights.

444
00:33:30.958 --> 00:33:33.166
I've been grooming that little prince for many cycles.

445
00:33:33.250 --> 00:33:34.875
setting him up for tomorrow's match.

446
00:33:34.958 --> 00:33:36.059
[The Mandalorian] Take the credits.

447
00:33:36.083 --> 00:33:38.291
It's his last fight for you anyway.

448
00:33:39.416 --> 00:33:40.666
It's his last fight ever.

449
00:33:42.291 --> 00:33:43.809
I've collected the most deadly creatures

450
00:33:43.833 --> 00:33:45.333
from across the galaxy.

451
00:33:45.875 --> 00:33:47.833
He's fighting a Dejarik match?

452
00:33:48.375 --> 00:33:49.500
Yes.

453
00:33:50.208 --> 00:33:51.791
He will die tomorrow.

454
00:33:52.958 --> 00:33:54.458
And a select few know it.

455
00:33:55.333 --> 00:33:56.666
Here's my gift to you:

456
00:33:57.708 --> 00:33:58.708
take those credits.

457
00:34:00.166 --> 00:34:02.000
bet it all on the death of the Hutt.

458
00:34:02.875 --> 00:34:04.291
In exchange.

459
00:34:04.375 --> 00:34:07.916
all I ask is that you consider fighting in my pit.

460
00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:10.166
The people of Shakari would pay any price

461
00:34:10.250 --> 00:34:12.125
to see the rarest of sights.

462
00:34:12.208 --> 00:34:15.000
one of the legendary Mandalorian warriors

463
00:34:15.083 --> 00:34:17.458
engaging in blood sport.

464
00:34:26.125 --> 00:34:27.541
This should more than cover

465
00:34:28.125 --> 00:34:30.083
our little misunderstanding out there.

466
00:34:34.041 --> 00:34:36.166
All I ask is that you consider my offer.

467
00:34:37.875 --> 00:34:40.166
Could make us both very rich.

468
00:34:50.125 --> 00:34:53.583
[pets fluttering. chittering]

469
00:35:00.458 --> 00:35:02.583
[♪ Dramatic electronic music playing]

470
00:35:14.458 --> 00:35:17.291
Looks like we're gonna have to do this the hard way.

471
00:35:19.125 --> 00:35:22.250
- [pit announcer speaking]
- [spectators cheering]

472
00:35:32.583 --> 00:35:34.666
- [gladiator opponent grunts]
- [Rotta roars]

473
00:36:30.000 --> 00:36:33.500
[snoring]

474
00:36:37.291 --> 00:36:40.208
[device beeping]

475
00:36:40.291 --> 00:36:42.250
[grunts]

476
00:36:43.250 --> 00:36:44.416
[shushes]

477
00:36:46.041 --> 00:36:47.416
What?

478
00:36:48.458 --> 00:36:50.041
Janu's planning on killing you.

479
00:36:50.125 --> 00:36:51.250
I'm here to get you out.

480
00:36:51.333 --> 00:36:54.500
[device continues beeping]

481
00:36:54.583 --> 00:36:57.500
Tomorrow's my last fight. I'll be free after I win.

482
00:36:57.583 --> 00:37:00.958
The fix is in. It's a Dejarik match.

483
00:37:01.041 --> 00:37:02.708
He will keep throwing opponents at you

484
00:37:02.791 --> 00:37:03.875
until you die.

485
00:37:03.958 --> 00:37:05.708
Why should I believe you?

486
00:37:06.208 --> 00:37:08.541
You were sent by my aunt and uncle who want me dead.

487
00:37:08.625 --> 00:37:10.250
They want you back.

488
00:37:10.333 --> 00:37:11.791
You're embarrassing them.

489
00:37:11.875 --> 00:37:13.017
[Rotta] The Twins want me dead

490
00:37:13.041 --> 00:37:15.625
because I'm heir to the throne. not them.

491
00:37:15.708 --> 00:37:17.250
But I don't want it.

492
00:37:17.333 --> 00:37:19.708
I don't wanna be anything like my father.

493
00:37:20.750 --> 00:37:23.833
When I first started fighting. the people all booed me.

494
00:37:23.916 --> 00:37:25.375
They wanted to see me die

495
00:37:25.458 --> 00:37:27.541
because I'm the son of Jabba the Hutt.

496
00:37:27.625 --> 00:37:29.416
Then I won and became a champion

497
00:37:29.500 --> 00:37:31.583
and they slowly began to cheer.

498
00:37:31.666 --> 00:37:33.666
They realized I'm not my father.

499
00:37:33.750 --> 00:37:35.166
I'm my own man.

500
00:37:35.250 --> 00:37:37.583
and I'm not afraid to fight for what I have.

501
00:37:37.666 --> 00:37:40.500
To earn it. To prove myself to everyone.

502
00:37:41.416 --> 00:37:44.041
[The Mandalorian] Kid. fighting's not a sport.

503
00:37:44.125 --> 00:37:45.958
It's a last resort.

504
00:37:46.041 --> 00:37:48.125
Now come with me before things get ugly.

505
00:37:48.208 --> 00:37:50.541
Guards. he's back!

506
00:37:50.625 --> 00:37:52.500
[♪ Tense music playing]

507
00:37:54.000 --> 00:37:57.000
[gasps] Get out. Get out!

508
00:37:57.083 --> 00:37:58.333
[coughing]

509
00:38:08.958 --> 00:38:09.958
[groans]

510
00:38:14.208 --> 00:38:15.250
[grunts]

511
00:38:33.708 --> 00:38:35.875
[crowd cheering in distance]

512
00:38:38.458 --> 00:38:40.250
[cheering intensifies]

513
00:38:42.000 --> 00:38:44.291
Rotta! Rotta! Rotta!

514
00:38:44.375 --> 00:38:46.458
[energy field powers down]

515
00:38:49.041 --> 00:38:51.000
[electricity buzzes]

516
00:38:55.166 --> 00:38:57.458
[crowd whistling and cheering]

517
00:39:02.833 --> 00:39:04.250
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

518
00:39:04.333 --> 00:39:06.250
[announcer] <i>Rotta!</i>

519
00:39:18.166 --> 00:39:19.333
[no audible dialogue]

520
00:39:22.791 --> 00:39:25.750
[squawking]

521
00:39:25.833 --> 00:39:27.250
[whimpers]

522
00:39:31.125 --> 00:39:32.125
[grunts]

523
00:39:33.333 --> 00:39:34.750
I don't want to fight you.

524
00:39:35.666 --> 00:39:37.708
Then you're in for a long day!

525
00:39:38.291 --> 00:39:41.875
- [Rotta shouting]
- [The Mandalorian grunting]

526
00:39:45.291 --> 00:39:47.083
[grunting]

527
00:39:47.166 --> 00:39:48.208
[chuckling] Yes!

528
00:39:48.291 --> 00:39:49.875
[straining]

529
00:39:49.958 --> 00:39:51.708
[grunts]

530
00:40:02.458 --> 00:40:03.500
[growls]

531
00:40:07.500 --> 00:40:09.458
- [Rotta shouts]
- [The Mandalorian grunts]

532
00:40:09.541 --> 00:40:10.708
[shouts]

533
00:40:12.666 --> 00:40:13.708
[sighs]

534
00:40:13.791 --> 00:40:16.541
- I'm not going to kill you.
- [choking]

535
00:40:16.625 --> 00:40:18.333
I'm here to rescue you.

536
00:40:18.416 --> 00:40:19.833
[shouts]

537
00:40:20.416 --> 00:40:21.851
- [Rotta grunts]
- [The Mandalorian groans]

538
00:40:21.875 --> 00:40:23.166
[sighs]

539
00:40:28.125 --> 00:40:30.208
[shouts]

540
00:40:32.958 --> 00:40:34.125
[whimpers]

541
00:40:34.208 --> 00:40:35.416
[groans]

542
00:40:38.375 --> 00:40:41.375
[shouting]

543
00:40:56.250 --> 00:40:58.041
[groans. grunts]

544
00:41:02.166 --> 00:41:03.625
[chuckles]

545
00:41:05.083 --> 00:41:07.375
[chanting] Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

546
00:41:07.458 --> 00:41:10.166
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

547
00:41:10.250 --> 00:41:12.875
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

548
00:41:12.958 --> 00:41:15.750
- Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!
- [Grogu whimpers]

549
00:41:15.833 --> 00:41:18.208
Kill! Kill! Kill! Kill!

550
00:41:18.291 --> 00:41:20.041
- Kill! Kill! Kill...
- [weapons clatter]

551
00:41:20.125 --> 00:41:21.291
I yield.

552
00:41:21.375 --> 00:41:24.666
[spectators booing]

553
00:41:25.875 --> 00:41:27.958
Rotta the Hutt has won.

554
00:41:28.041 --> 00:41:30.708
Now you owe him his freedom.

555
00:41:33.375 --> 00:41:35.208
[booing continues]

556
00:41:37.750 --> 00:41:39.833
[echoing. through speakers] Rotta the Hutt has won.

557
00:41:40.583 --> 00:41:42.500
Now he is free...

558
00:41:45.166 --> 00:41:46.291
to die!

559
00:41:46.375 --> 00:41:47.541
[♪ Perilous music playing]

560
00:41:47.625 --> 00:41:48.916
[spectators cheering]

561
00:41:51.041 --> 00:41:53.041
[energy field powers up]

562
00:42:04.833 --> 00:42:07.291
[footsteps rumble]

563
00:42:13.041 --> 00:42:14.500
[roars]

564
00:42:19.791 --> 00:42:21.416
[bellows]

565
00:42:23.250 --> 00:42:25.083
[electricity crackles]

566
00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:29.875
- [shrieks]
- [electricity buzzes]

567
00:42:32.041 --> 00:42:34.833
Our only chance is to work together.

568
00:42:45.291 --> 00:42:47.250
[chittering. hissing]

569
00:42:55.791 --> 00:42:58.833
[warbling]

570
00:42:58.916 --> 00:43:00.583
[growling]

571
00:43:01.916 --> 00:43:03.041
[The Mandalorian grunts]

572
00:43:09.750 --> 00:43:10.916
[The Mandalorian grunts]

573
00:43:12.875 --> 00:43:13.875
[grunts]

574
00:43:14.500 --> 00:43:16.375
- [electricity crackles]
- [hisses]

575
00:43:20.625 --> 00:43:21.625
[The Mandalorian groans]

576
00:43:22.541 --> 00:43:24.500
[Rotta shouting]

577
00:43:28.500 --> 00:43:30.541
- [Rotta shouting]
- [The Mandalorian grunts]

578
00:43:30.625 --> 00:43:32.958
[The Mandalorian grunting]

579
00:43:33.041 --> 00:43:34.083
[groans]

580
00:43:36.166 --> 00:43:38.000
- [bellowing]
- [The Mandalorian grunts]

581
00:43:38.583 --> 00:43:39.583
- [bellows]
- [grunts]

582
00:43:44.500 --> 00:43:46.416
[laughing]

583
00:43:47.500 --> 00:43:49.583
[warbling]

584
00:43:55.000 --> 00:43:56.125
[roars]

585
00:43:57.791 --> 00:43:58.958
[shrieks]

586
00:43:59.041 --> 00:44:00.851
[The Mandalorian] Watch out for the little one.

587
00:44:00.875 --> 00:44:02.166
Yeah. I got this.

588
00:44:02.833 --> 00:44:05.750
- [shouting]
- [electricity buzzes]

589
00:44:09.916 --> 00:44:11.041
[shrieking]

590
00:44:21.791 --> 00:44:23.208
[grunts]

591
00:44:26.291 --> 00:44:27.291
[The Mandalorian grunts]

592
00:44:32.750 --> 00:44:34.875
[grunting]

593
00:44:37.083 --> 00:44:38.083
[Rotta shouts]

594
00:44:39.250 --> 00:44:42.541
[shouting]

595
00:44:45.416 --> 00:44:46.416
[The Mandalorian grunts]

596
00:44:47.250 --> 00:44:48.250
[shouts]

597
00:44:49.833 --> 00:44:51.250
[roars]

598
00:44:52.125 --> 00:44:53.875
- [shrieks]
- [electricity crackles]

599
00:44:53.958 --> 00:44:56.125
[Rotta shouting]

600
00:44:56.208 --> 00:44:57.250
[shouts]

601
00:44:58.916 --> 00:45:00.458
[energy barrier powers down]

602
00:45:00.541 --> 00:45:02.416
[spectators exclaiming]

603
00:45:05.916 --> 00:45:09.375
[alarm blaring]

604
00:45:09.458 --> 00:45:10.458
[grunts]

605
00:45:13.250 --> 00:45:14.250
We should go now.

606
00:45:14.333 --> 00:45:15.500
Now!

607
00:45:19.333 --> 00:45:21.125
[spectators screaming]

608
00:45:23.708 --> 00:45:26.250
[screaming]

609
00:45:45.791 --> 00:45:46.791
Are you good?

610
00:45:48.291 --> 00:45:50.708
Don't worry. buddy. We're getting out of here.

611
00:45:56.500 --> 00:45:57.500
[whimpers]

612
00:46:04.875 --> 00:46:05.958
[screaming]

613
00:46:06.583 --> 00:46:08.791
[chokes. screams]

614
00:46:13.625 --> 00:46:15.833
You were right. The fix was in.

615
00:46:15.916 --> 00:46:17.375
Let's get you out of here.

616
00:46:17.458 --> 00:46:18.500
[warbling]

617
00:46:19.125 --> 00:46:20.750
I'm gonna find us a ride.

618
00:46:32.000 --> 00:46:33.333
[grunting]

619
00:46:35.333 --> 00:46:36.458
[screams]

620
00:46:39.666 --> 00:46:40.916
[babbles]

621
00:46:43.041 --> 00:46:44.291
Sorry. Mando.

622
00:46:44.375 --> 00:46:45.833
I can't go back.

623
00:46:51.291 --> 00:46:54.708
[whirring and powering up]

624
00:46:55.500 --> 00:46:56.666
[Grogu squeals]

625
00:47:00.666 --> 00:47:01.791
[shrieks]

626
00:47:01.875 --> 00:47:03.333
[Rotta shouts]

627
00:47:09.208 --> 00:47:11.041
Zeb. I got a runner.

628
00:47:24.041 --> 00:47:25.166
[gasps]

629
00:47:26.000 --> 00:47:27.250
[screams]

630
00:47:34.583 --> 00:47:36.791
[pedestrians screaming]

631
00:47:55.750 --> 00:47:56.750
[Rotta groans]

632
00:48:01.500 --> 00:48:03.708
Okay. you got me.

633
00:48:04.750 --> 00:48:06.666
Can't blame a guy for trying.

634
00:48:14.625 --> 00:48:15.791
[♪ Calm music playing]

635
00:48:24.666 --> 00:48:26.875
[The Mandalorian] We're about to jump to hyperspace.

636
00:48:26.958 --> 00:48:28.375
Where are you bringing me?

637
00:48:28.458 --> 00:48:30.208
It's not safe to keep you chained up.

638
00:48:30.708 --> 00:48:31.916
If I unlock you.

639
00:48:32.000 --> 00:48:33.958
can we agree to no funny stuff?

640
00:48:34.041 --> 00:48:36.083
Are you bringing me to Nal Hutta?

641
00:48:36.166 --> 00:48:37.250
This is an old ship.

642
00:48:37.333 --> 00:48:39.250
Sometimes things get a little bouncy.

643
00:48:39.833 --> 00:48:42.125
My aunt and uncle were scared of my father.

644
00:48:42.208 --> 00:48:44.208
They've always been cruel to me.

645
00:48:44.291 --> 00:48:46.416
Now that they control his criminal empire.

646
00:48:46.500 --> 00:48:48.166
they need me eliminated.

647
00:48:48.250 --> 00:48:50.333
You bring me to them. I'm a dead man.

648
00:48:50.416 --> 00:48:51.458
You don't know that.

649
00:48:51.541 --> 00:48:52.625
[Rotta] If you let me go.

650
00:48:52.708 --> 00:48:54.458
you'll never hear from me again.

651
00:48:54.958 --> 00:48:56.625
It's a big galaxy.

652
00:48:56.708 --> 00:48:57.916
I can disappear.

653
00:48:58.000 --> 00:48:59.666
Sorry. kid.

654
00:48:59.750 --> 00:49:01.333
I was hired to do a job.

655
00:49:01.916 --> 00:49:04.125
I don't know how you sleep at night.

656
00:49:04.208 --> 00:49:05.791
working for those monsters.

657
00:49:06.333 --> 00:49:08.166
I don't work for them.

658
00:49:08.250 --> 00:49:10.291
I work for the New Republic.

659
00:49:10.375 --> 00:49:12.791
They hired me. not the Twins.

660
00:49:13.291 --> 00:49:14.916
When I bring you back. they're giving me

661
00:49:15.000 --> 00:49:16.708
the whereabouts of Commander Coin.

662
00:49:16.791 --> 00:49:19.750
a high-ranking ex-Imperial operating on the Outer Rim.

663
00:49:20.250 --> 00:49:21.541
[Rotta] It's Janu.

664
00:49:22.666 --> 00:49:25.541
The man you're looking for is Janu.

665
00:49:25.625 --> 00:49:27.000
Lord Janu Coin.

666
00:49:27.500 --> 00:49:29.017
That's who the Hutts are gonna give you.

667
00:49:29.041 --> 00:49:30.333
He's ex-Imperial.

668
00:49:30.416 --> 00:49:32.750
That can't be. The Twins would've told me.

669
00:49:32.833 --> 00:49:34.458
[Rotta] I saw stormtroopers.

670
00:49:35.375 --> 00:49:37.000
He brought me to his estate once

671
00:49:37.083 --> 00:49:38.166
to celebrate a big win

672
00:49:38.250 --> 00:49:40.500
and there were stormtroopers everywhere.

673
00:49:40.583 --> 00:49:42.583
If you don't believe me and you don't get him now.

674
00:49:42.625 --> 00:49:44.041
you won't get another shot.

675
00:49:44.541 --> 00:49:46.208
In fact. it might already be too late.

676
00:49:47.083 --> 00:49:48.625
That's quite a story.

677
00:49:48.708 --> 00:49:50.416
Why should I believe you?

678
00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:53.541
You're a bounty hunter. you know when someone's lying.

679
00:49:55.916 --> 00:49:57.500
Am I lying...

680
00:49:57.583 --> 00:49:59.250
or am I telling the truth?

681
00:50:19.958 --> 00:50:21.083
[Rotta] That's it.

682
00:50:21.666 --> 00:50:23.583
That's Janu Coin's compound.

683
00:50:24.416 --> 00:50:27.000
[Zeb] Could be big boy's telling the truth.

684
00:50:27.083 --> 00:50:29.750
The place is lousy with stormtroopers.

685
00:50:33.208 --> 00:50:34.476
[The Mandalorian] How many did you see

686
00:50:34.500 --> 00:50:35.500
when you were in there?

687
00:50:36.458 --> 00:50:37.458
[Rotta] A lot.

688
00:50:37.541 --> 00:50:38.458
[Grogu babbles]

689
00:50:38.541 --> 00:50:39.875
You're gonna need a lot of backup

690
00:50:39.958 --> 00:50:41.791
if you're actually thinking of going in.

691
00:50:42.708 --> 00:50:43.833
Uh-huh.

692
00:50:45.125 --> 00:50:47.083
[Janu Coin] Get word to all our foot soldiers

693
00:50:47.166 --> 00:50:49.083
on the dark side of Shakari.

694
00:50:49.166 --> 00:50:52.833
I want eyes on the star port and all the freight lanes.

695
00:50:52.916 --> 00:50:53.916
Lean on the mayor.

696
00:50:54.000 --> 00:50:56.250
Nothing takes off or lands until we find them.

697
00:50:56.333 --> 00:50:58.416
Muster my personal security forces.

698
00:50:59.041 --> 00:51:01.250
We're going to hit the streets in full armor.

699
00:51:01.333 --> 00:51:02.613
I don't want to take any chances

700
00:51:02.666 --> 00:51:04.041
when it comes to The Mandalorian.

701
00:51:04.125 --> 00:51:06.416
I've heard many things about those monsters.

702
00:51:06.916 --> 00:51:08.250
[The Mandalorian] It's all true.

703
00:51:09.750 --> 00:51:11.916
Imperial Commander Janu Coin.

704
00:51:12.000 --> 00:51:13.750
I'm here on behalf of the New Republic

705
00:51:13.833 --> 00:51:15.375
to bring you to justice.

706
00:51:16.000 --> 00:51:18.500
I'm afraid we're outside of your jurisdiction.

707
00:51:19.250 --> 00:51:20.541
Take him!

708
00:51:20.625 --> 00:51:22.458
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

709
00:51:25.375 --> 00:51:26.958
- Set blasters on full.
- Hurry!

710
00:51:27.041 --> 00:51:30.500
[grunting. shouts]

711
00:51:34.750 --> 00:51:36.083
[grunts]

712
00:51:37.958 --> 00:51:39.458
- [grunts]
- [screams]

713
00:51:46.416 --> 00:51:47.833
[Hogsbreth shouts]

714
00:51:55.750 --> 00:51:58.000
[Hogsbreth grunts]

715
00:51:58.083 --> 00:51:59.666
[shouts]

716
00:52:02.916 --> 00:52:03.958
[choking]

717
00:52:07.041 --> 00:52:09.916
[both straining]

718
00:52:10.000 --> 00:52:11.500
- [Hogsbreth shouts]
- [grunting]

719
00:52:14.166 --> 00:52:15.000
[shouts]

720
00:52:15.083 --> 00:52:16.375
[groans]

721
00:52:16.458 --> 00:52:19.083
- [grunting]
- [choking]

722
00:52:19.750 --> 00:52:21.583
[screams]

723
00:52:26.250 --> 00:52:28.083
I can bring you in warm...

724
00:52:29.666 --> 00:52:31.583
or I can bring you in cold.

725
00:52:33.333 --> 00:52:34.916
[♪ Adventurous music playing]

726
00:52:35.000 --> 00:52:37.791
[Zeb grunting]

727
00:52:41.833 --> 00:52:43.041
[Janu Coin shouts]

728
00:52:51.916 --> 00:52:55.500
[Rotta. Grogu snoring]

729
00:52:55.583 --> 00:52:56.983
[The Mandalorian over comms] <i>Grogu.</i>

730
00:52:57.041 --> 00:52:58.416
[♪ Peaceful music playing]

731
00:52:58.500 --> 00:52:59.625
[The Mandalorian] <i>Rotta.</i>

732
00:53:00.333 --> 00:53:01.791
<i>Rotta. come in.</i>

733
00:53:01.875 --> 00:53:03.250
<i>Does anyone read me?</i>

734
00:53:03.333 --> 00:53:04.750
- [babbles]
- [thuds]

735
00:53:04.833 --> 00:53:06.041
I'm up. I'm up.

736
00:53:06.125 --> 00:53:08.291
[The Mandalorian] <i>I need you to fire up the drives.</i>

737
00:53:08.375 --> 00:53:09.458
<i>Fire up the drives.</i>

738
00:53:09.541 --> 00:53:11.291
<i>- We have company.</i>
- Received.

739
00:53:12.041 --> 00:53:14.375
I don't know how to fly. Do you know how to fly?

740
00:53:15.166 --> 00:53:16.833
Neither of us know how to fly.

741
00:53:16.916 --> 00:53:18.625
and I can't even fit in the cockpit.

742
00:53:25.125 --> 00:53:28.500
Grogu. I need you to go to the control panel.

743
00:53:28.583 --> 00:53:30.583
Remember the buttons I told you never to touch?

744
00:53:30.666 --> 00:53:32.291
<i>I'm gonna need you to touch them.</i>

745
00:53:32.375 --> 00:53:35.125
<i>Look for the ignition relay cutoff.</i>

746
00:53:35.208 --> 00:53:37.333
<i>It's next to the fuel differential readout.</i>

747
00:53:37.875 --> 00:53:40.666
<i>which is between the pump compression gauge</i>

748
00:53:40.750 --> 00:53:42.541
<i>and the primary reserve indic...</i>

749
00:53:42.625 --> 00:53:43.791
[missile whooshes]

750
00:53:45.125 --> 00:53:46.541
- [Janu Coin grunts]
- [Zeb] Whoa.

751
00:53:46.625 --> 00:53:49.125
No. Don't touch the missile battery switch.

752
00:53:49.208 --> 00:53:50.833
<i>That's why there's a safety guard on it.</i>

753
00:53:50.916 --> 00:53:53.041
<i>Do you see the fuel readout display?</i>

754
00:53:53.125 --> 00:53:54.583
Remember I showed you that one?

755
00:53:54.666 --> 00:53:55.833
<i>It's on the other side</i>

756
00:53:55.916 --> 00:53:58.250
<i>of the manual control surface calibration un...</i>

757
00:53:58.333 --> 00:53:59.458
[missile whooshes]

758
00:54:00.958 --> 00:54:02.833
I don't think he knows what he's doing.

759
00:54:12.750 --> 00:54:14.041
[screams]

760
00:54:25.208 --> 00:54:26.333
Get out.

761
00:54:26.416 --> 00:54:28.041
[grunting]

762
00:54:30.875 --> 00:54:33.375
Get going. They're shooting at you too.

763
00:54:35.250 --> 00:54:36.291
[whimpers]

764
00:54:39.083 --> 00:54:40.500
[shouts]

765
00:54:41.750 --> 00:54:43.708
Good job. buddy. Strap in.

766
00:54:56.583 --> 00:54:58.958
- [grunts. shouts]
- [stormtroopers scream]

767
00:55:04.666 --> 00:55:07.750
[panting]

768
00:55:08.375 --> 00:55:09.916
I like this kid.

769
00:55:20.583 --> 00:55:22.416
Come on. Come on.

770
00:55:34.666 --> 00:55:36.541
Get us out of atmosphere and jump!

771
00:55:36.625 --> 00:55:37.666
Get up here.

772
00:55:37.750 --> 00:55:39.750
I need you to bypass the exhaust restrictors.

773
00:55:53.583 --> 00:55:56.000
[groans] This old junker's gonna get us killed.

774
00:55:56.083 --> 00:55:57.208
I need more power.

775
00:55:57.291 --> 00:55:59.958
Disable the safety panel so I can override the limiter.

776
00:56:00.041 --> 00:56:02.708
How? I'm a pilot. not a meknek.

777
00:56:02.791 --> 00:56:04.916
Just rip out the whole brain board.

778
00:56:05.416 --> 00:56:07.541
[groaning]

779
00:56:07.625 --> 00:56:08.833
[systems power down]

780
00:56:08.916 --> 00:56:10.333
[alarm blares]

781
00:56:10.416 --> 00:56:12.000
Everything okay up there?

782
00:56:12.083 --> 00:56:13.500
Perfect.

783
00:56:17.166 --> 00:56:18.208
[whimpers]

784
00:56:20.208 --> 00:56:22.958
I told you to strap in. Always wear your seat belt.

785
00:56:28.000 --> 00:56:29.000
[both shout]

786
00:56:31.208 --> 00:56:32.291
[Zeb groans]

787
00:56:32.375 --> 00:56:34.250
Take it easy up there!

788
00:56:40.625 --> 00:56:41.958
There we go.

789
00:56:53.125 --> 00:56:54.125
[giggles]

790
00:57:08.500 --> 00:57:12.291
[targeting system beeping]

791
00:57:49.958 --> 00:57:51.416
[Janu Coin clears throat]

792
00:57:53.375 --> 00:57:55.750
[chattering]

793
00:58:01.666 --> 00:58:03.083
[chattering stops]

794
00:58:13.791 --> 00:58:15.625
That doesn't look like a Hutt.

795
00:58:15.708 --> 00:58:18.416
This is Imperial Commander Janu Coin.

796
00:58:18.500 --> 00:58:21.666
He's full of information and ready to sing like a Yuzzum.

797
00:58:21.750 --> 00:58:23.416
Isn't that right. Coin?

798
00:58:23.500 --> 00:58:24.916
I demand an attorney be present

799
00:58:25.000 --> 00:58:26.166
if I'm to be questioned.

800
00:58:26.833 --> 00:58:27.833
You see?

801
00:58:28.333 --> 00:58:30.041
He's full of secrets.

802
00:58:30.875 --> 00:58:32.666
You were supposed to bring back Rotta.

803
00:58:33.791 --> 00:58:36.041
We had an arrangement with the Twins.

804
00:58:36.125 --> 00:58:38.208
This is your Ace of Staves.

805
00:58:38.958 --> 00:58:40.958
This is who they were going to lead you to.

806
00:58:41.666 --> 00:58:42.791
And then tip him off.

807
00:58:42.875 --> 00:58:45.500
sell you out and collect credits from both sides.

808
00:58:46.708 --> 00:58:48.083
Take him away.

809
00:58:53.166 --> 00:58:55.083
Intelligence has been cultivating

810
00:58:55.166 --> 00:58:58.333
a relationship with the Hutts for a very long time.

811
00:58:58.416 --> 00:58:59.916
and you crossed them.

812
00:59:01.375 --> 00:59:03.166
The Twins can hold a grudge.

813
00:59:03.250 --> 00:59:04.500
I made a call.

814
00:59:04.583 --> 00:59:06.208
I got you the big prize.

815
00:59:06.750 --> 00:59:08.708
The Twins can rot in hell.

816
00:59:08.791 --> 00:59:10.226
Well. you missed out on them paying you

817
00:59:10.250 --> 00:59:12.208
a big bounty for their nephew.

818
00:59:12.291 --> 00:59:13.416
Hmm...

819
00:59:13.500 --> 00:59:14.791
So be it.

820
00:59:16.791 --> 00:59:18.833
Well. I'll see if I can hit up Command

821
00:59:18.916 --> 00:59:20.833
for a fee for the capture of Coin.

822
00:59:20.916 --> 00:59:23.416
Don't worry about it. It's on me.

823
00:59:24.208 --> 00:59:25.791
This one got messy.

824
00:59:25.875 --> 00:59:27.125
I'm taking a break.

825
00:59:28.708 --> 00:59:30.041
I understand.

826
00:59:31.083 --> 00:59:32.291
Mando.

827
00:59:34.958 --> 00:59:36.208
Good job.

828
00:59:49.666 --> 00:59:51.666
[Grogu giggling. babbling]

829
00:59:56.916 --> 00:59:58.333
[Rotta chuckles]

830
01:00:02.166 --> 01:00:04.291
[♪ Uplifting music plays]

831
01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:51.208
[♪ Ominous music plays]

832
01:00:56.500 --> 01:00:58.083
[♪ Music stops]

833
01:01:00.583 --> 01:01:02.642
[The Mandalorian] We're gonna pull the restrict or plates.

834
01:01:02.666 --> 01:01:05.333
The first one should be just past the return line.

835
01:01:05.416 --> 01:01:06.916
That's it.

836
01:01:07.000 --> 01:01:09.125
- There should be three more.
- [vehicle approaches]

837
01:01:12.458 --> 01:01:14.666
[heads-up display beeping]

838
01:01:21.708 --> 01:01:24.000
Okay. okay. Okey-doke.

839
01:01:27.166 --> 01:01:29.250
[♪ Whimsical music plays]

840
01:01:30.125 --> 01:01:31.125
[Anzellan 1] Okay. okay.

841
01:01:31.208 --> 01:01:32.541
Thanks for coming.

842
01:01:33.208 --> 01:01:34.500
No problem.

843
01:01:34.583 --> 01:01:37.375
I'm looking to make some performance modifications.

844
01:01:37.458 --> 01:01:39.250
I need to cut out dead weight for speed.

845
01:01:39.333 --> 01:01:40.583
[exclaims. chuckles]

846
01:01:40.666 --> 01:01:43.000
Pull out anything that doesn't make her go.

847
01:01:43.833 --> 01:01:44.833
[The Mandalorian] Hey!

848
01:01:44.916 --> 01:01:46.309
- [chattering]
- [The Mandalorian] Hey. Hey.

849
01:01:46.333 --> 01:01:47.333
No. don't touch me!

850
01:01:47.416 --> 01:01:49.750
- Heel.
- [Grogu groans]

851
01:01:49.833 --> 01:01:51.541
- The horrible baby.
- The bad baby.

852
01:01:51.625 --> 01:01:53.583
- Stay.
- [sighs]

853
01:01:53.666 --> 01:01:55.059
[The Mandalorian] I purged the fuel lines.

854
01:01:55.083 --> 01:01:56.750
I wanna remove all the restrictors

855
01:01:56.833 --> 01:01:58.416
and unplug the exhaust.

856
01:01:58.500 --> 01:02:01.583
- Got it. Yeah. yeah.
- No problem. Yeah. I got it.

857
01:02:02.208 --> 01:02:03.458
- No problem.
- Yeah. Okey-doke.

858
01:02:04.916 --> 01:02:06.166
You wanna go help them?

859
01:02:08.041 --> 01:02:09.791
Do you promise to play nice?

860
01:02:09.875 --> 01:02:11.083
[exclaims]

861
01:02:11.166 --> 01:02:13.250
All right. Go.

862
01:02:13.333 --> 01:02:15.250
[giggles]

863
01:02:15.333 --> 01:02:17.333
[speaking Anzellan]

864
01:02:19.875 --> 01:02:21.075
[Rotta] Don't worry about him.

865
01:02:23.375 --> 01:02:25.125
Little guy's gonna be okay.

866
01:02:25.208 --> 01:02:26.791
[crunches]

867
01:02:27.291 --> 01:02:29.291
Sorry. I found these in your kitchen.

868
01:02:29.375 --> 01:02:31.666
[Rotta chewing]

869
01:02:33.125 --> 01:02:34.916
I was alone when I was his age.

870
01:02:35.791 --> 01:02:37.333
I had to fend for myself.

871
01:02:42.708 --> 01:02:43.958
He's lucky he has you.

872
01:02:44.833 --> 01:02:47.708
Well. you didn't turn out half bad.

873
01:02:49.125 --> 01:02:52.750
Mmm. Life's messy. but we do the best we can.

874
01:02:54.333 --> 01:02:56.000
Listen. I called a gunrunner

875
01:02:56.083 --> 01:02:57.833
who agreed to take you out of the system.

876
01:02:57.916 --> 01:02:59.796
We both know the Twins will be looking for you.

877
01:02:59.875 --> 01:03:01.250
so you best keep moving.

878
01:03:01.791 --> 01:03:03.583
[♪ Gentle music playing]

879
01:03:26.458 --> 01:03:27.833
Thank you. Mando.

880
01:03:27.916 --> 01:03:29.375
It was a fair trade.

881
01:03:29.458 --> 01:03:31.375
Make sure you lay low.

882
01:03:31.458 --> 01:03:33.791
I don't wanna see your name on my list again.

883
01:03:33.875 --> 01:03:35.083
You have my word.

884
01:03:36.208 --> 01:03:38.458
All right. you take care of yourself. little guy.

885
01:03:40.000 --> 01:03:42.916
And keep an eye on your old man. too. all right?

886
01:03:43.916 --> 01:03:45.291
Here you go.

887
01:03:45.375 --> 01:03:47.083
Hang on to these for me.

888
01:04:06.083 --> 01:04:08.375
[♪ Triumphant music playing]

889
01:04:24.166 --> 01:04:25.708
[crunches]

890
01:04:25.791 --> 01:04:27.500
[exclaims. babbles]

891
01:04:28.250 --> 01:04:30.583
Let's save the rest of these for after dinner.

892
01:04:31.375 --> 01:04:33.916
[scoffs. chews]

893
01:04:43.708 --> 01:04:45.916
- [insects chirping]
- [thunder rumbles]

894
01:05:02.333 --> 01:05:04.500
[blurrg bellows]

895
01:05:04.583 --> 01:05:06.708
[blurrg bellows]

896
01:05:09.500 --> 01:05:11.625
[blurrg groans]

897
01:05:22.750 --> 01:05:24.125
[heads-up display beeps. whirs]

898
01:05:45.375 --> 01:05:47.250
[snoring]

899
01:05:48.333 --> 01:05:50.267
- [The Mandalorian] Wake up.
- [Grogu breathes heavily]

900
01:05:50.291 --> 01:05:51.291
Oh. What? Uh.

901
01:05:51.375 --> 01:05:52.767
- [The Mandalorian] Wake up.
- What's going on?

902
01:05:52.791 --> 01:05:54.041
There's someone out there.

903
01:05:54.125 --> 01:05:55.642
[Anzellan 1] I'll be awake in the morning.

904
01:05:55.666 --> 01:05:57.500
[The Mandalorian] Quiet. Get under the floor.

905
01:05:57.583 --> 01:05:58.708
[button beeps]

906
01:06:01.208 --> 01:06:03.541
[thunderclap]

907
01:06:06.250 --> 01:06:07.610
- [shutter closes]
- [Grogu grunts]

908
01:06:09.416 --> 01:06:12.708
Wait here. If I signal. get out.

909
01:06:19.458 --> 01:06:21.041
[heads-up display beeps. whirs]

910
01:06:31.416 --> 01:06:33.416
[Anzellan 1 gasping]

911
01:06:33.500 --> 01:06:35.875
- [metal clangs]
- Shh. Shh. Shh.

912
01:06:42.083 --> 01:06:43.375
[device beeping]

913
01:06:45.625 --> 01:06:47.583
[Grogu panting]

914
01:06:47.666 --> 01:06:49.791
[device beeping]

915
01:06:53.375 --> 01:06:54.375
[device whirs]

916
01:06:54.416 --> 01:06:55.708
[The Mandalorian groans]

917
01:06:55.791 --> 01:06:58.291
[♪ Tense music plays]

918
01:07:05.958 --> 01:07:07.541
[panting]

919
01:07:14.916 --> 01:07:16.666
[growling]

920
01:07:16.750 --> 01:07:18.375
[screaming]

921
01:07:19.916 --> 01:07:22.208
[grunts. groans]

922
01:07:23.958 --> 01:07:27.041
- [screaming]
- Help! It got me! It got me!

923
01:07:27.125 --> 01:07:29.333
[Embo whistles] Keibu. [Speaks Kyuzo]

924
01:07:31.375 --> 01:07:33.125
[♪ Mysterious music playing]

925
01:08:02.833 --> 01:08:04.833
[engine revs]

926
01:08:22.250 --> 01:08:24.416
[in Huttese] Did you get the Mandalorian?

927
01:08:24.500 --> 01:08:25.583
[speaks Huttese]

928
01:08:25.666 --> 01:08:29.458
[Hutt sister] Very good. Bring him to Nal Hutta.

929
01:08:29.541 --> 01:08:30.708
[Grogu babbles]

930
01:08:37.541 --> 01:08:39.083
Help me! Help!

931
01:09:09.000 --> 01:09:10.166
[groans]

932
01:09:14.041 --> 01:09:16.791
[groaning]

933
01:09:19.125 --> 01:09:20.500
[sighs]

934
01:09:22.750 --> 01:09:25.208
[breathing heavily]

935
01:09:31.166 --> 01:09:33.625
[groans. sighs]

936
01:09:36.208 --> 01:09:38.375
- [grunting]
- [Keibu growling]

937
01:09:39.458 --> 01:09:41.666
[panting] Ow.

938
01:09:43.208 --> 01:09:45.458
[exclaims] Ow. ow. ow.

939
01:09:47.333 --> 01:09:48.583
Let him go.

940
01:09:49.375 --> 01:09:50.916
[rumbling]

941
01:09:55.458 --> 01:09:57.208
Hey. you hungry?

942
01:10:01.458 --> 01:10:02.958
You want a treat?

943
01:10:04.791 --> 01:10:06.208
Here you go.

944
01:10:06.291 --> 01:10:08.083
- Good girl.
- [snarls]

945
01:10:09.375 --> 01:10:10.375
Come on. Come on!

946
01:10:10.458 --> 01:10:12.500
[whimpering. panting] Uh-oh.

947
01:10:12.583 --> 01:10:13.916
Oh. [Straining]

948
01:10:14.000 --> 01:10:16.333
- [growls]
- [Anzellan 1 screaming]

949
01:10:18.208 --> 01:10:19.625
[panting]

950
01:10:19.708 --> 01:10:21.541
[barks. snarls]

951
01:10:23.958 --> 01:10:25.833
[machine whirring]

952
01:10:25.916 --> 01:10:28.125
[♪ Mysterious music playing]

953
01:10:33.625 --> 01:10:35.291
Uh-oh.

954
01:10:40.333 --> 01:10:41.958
Who hired you?

955
01:10:42.708 --> 01:10:44.166
Was it the Hutts?

956
01:10:45.708 --> 01:10:47.291
Well. if it was the Hutts.

957
01:10:47.375 --> 01:10:49.458
I'd make sure they're paying you what you're worth.

958
01:10:49.541 --> 01:10:51.208
But I'm guessing a Kyuzo is smart enough

959
01:10:51.291 --> 01:10:52.351
to get their money up-front...

960
01:10:52.375 --> 01:10:54.083
[groaning]

961
01:11:02.583 --> 01:11:04.208
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

962
01:11:24.041 --> 01:11:25.666
[engine starting up]

963
01:11:30.083 --> 01:11:31.791
[devices beeping]

964
01:11:47.166 --> 01:11:49.041
[♪ Ominous music playing]

965
01:12:19.333 --> 01:12:20.958
[exclaims]

966
01:12:49.291 --> 01:12:51.291
Nal Hutta.

967
01:12:51.375 --> 01:12:54.583
The Hutts are there. I don't like it.

968
01:13:01.458 --> 01:13:03.250
[screeching]

969
01:13:14.416 --> 01:13:16.208
Oh! Wow! Oh. I'm coming.

970
01:13:24.125 --> 01:13:25.392
[Anzellan 2] Kid. don't be scared.

971
01:13:25.416 --> 01:13:27.166
Don't be scared. It's okay. yeah.

972
01:13:27.250 --> 01:13:28.333
Come on. let's go.

973
01:13:28.416 --> 01:13:30.125
- [rustling]
- Oh...

974
01:13:31.583 --> 01:13:33.541
[footsteps approaching]

975
01:13:40.541 --> 01:13:43.625
Oh! Hello! It's me. it's me! You're here.

976
01:13:43.708 --> 01:13:46.416
You came for me! You found me!

977
01:13:47.750 --> 01:13:49.458
[Anzellan 2] Oh. we thought you were dead.

978
01:13:50.416 --> 01:13:52.000
Mandalorian. he saved me.

979
01:13:52.083 --> 01:13:54.125
Big guy. He's inside there.

980
01:13:54.208 --> 01:13:56.083
Yeah. we got to go and find him

981
01:13:56.166 --> 01:13:57.958
and bring him home for the baby.

982
01:13:59.833 --> 01:14:02.791
The big thing. The big dog. The big dog. The big...

983
01:14:02.875 --> 01:14:04.875
Oh. oh. It picked me up...

984
01:14:16.000 --> 01:14:18.541
Mando is in there. In the palace.

985
01:14:31.291 --> 01:14:32.958
Come on. Up. up. up. up.

986
01:14:33.041 --> 01:14:34.875
Come on. baby. You can do it.

987
01:14:43.166 --> 01:14:44.916
Big pipe. huh?

988
01:15:09.208 --> 01:15:10.875
[roars]

989
01:15:13.291 --> 01:15:14.791
Good shot. baby.

990
01:15:14.875 --> 01:15:16.583
[♪ Ominous music plays]

991
01:15:18.916 --> 01:15:21.333
[Keibu pants. growls]

992
01:15:21.416 --> 01:15:22.708
[metal clangs]

993
01:15:35.000 --> 01:15:36.041
[The Mandalorian grunts]

994
01:15:37.041 --> 01:15:39.458
[in Huttese] Pay the hunter.

995
01:15:39.541 --> 01:15:41.375
[footsteps clanging]

996
01:15:55.041 --> 01:15:58.208
[in English] You broke our agreement.

997
01:15:58.291 --> 01:16:00.458
Now you must pay.

998
01:16:01.250 --> 01:16:02.916
[in Huttese] Bring me his helmet.

999
01:16:03.791 --> 01:16:04.791
[air hisses]

1000
01:16:07.041 --> 01:16:09.416
[♪ Pensive music plays]

1001
01:16:13.000 --> 01:16:15.875
[in English] Mandalorian steel.

1002
01:16:15.958 --> 01:16:19.666
Priceless on the black market.

1003
01:16:21.041 --> 01:16:24.458
But worth even more is knowing

1004
01:16:24.541 --> 01:16:28.250
we have shamed you forever.

1005
01:16:28.875 --> 01:16:31.625
[Hutt brother] We know the Mandalorian Creed.

1006
01:16:32.166 --> 01:16:33.916
You will be outcast

1007
01:16:34.000 --> 01:16:37.416
for letting an enemy see your face.

1008
01:16:38.083 --> 01:16:39.708
Not if you all die.

1009
01:16:41.291 --> 01:16:43.333
[chuckles]

1010
01:16:43.416 --> 01:16:46.791
It will bring us ecstasy

1011
01:16:46.875 --> 01:16:51.708
to watch your strong spirit break.

1012
01:16:53.708 --> 01:16:55.208
[electricity zaps]

1013
01:16:56.000 --> 01:16:58.416
- [electricity zaps. buzzing]
- [groaning]

1014
01:17:00.791 --> 01:17:01.791
Monsters.

1015
01:17:02.500 --> 01:17:04.208
[Hutt brother] You did this to him.

1016
01:17:04.291 --> 01:17:07.583
Rotta would have died painlessly.

1017
01:17:07.666 --> 01:17:09.083
but you betrayed us.

1018
01:17:09.583 --> 01:17:13.083
Now he will suffer for centuries.

1019
01:17:13.625 --> 01:17:18.666
You see. Hutts live for hundreds of years.

1020
01:17:19.458 --> 01:17:24.000
Just like your small. green child.

1021
01:17:24.500 --> 01:17:26.583
One day you will die.

1022
01:17:26.666 --> 01:17:30.541
and Grogu will be without you to protect him.

1023
01:17:30.625 --> 01:17:34.500
And then. it will be his turn to suffer.

1024
01:17:35.458 --> 01:17:37.375
- [mechanism whirs]
- [grunts]

1025
01:17:48.666 --> 01:17:50.541
[♪ Tense music plays]

1026
01:17:55.875 --> 01:17:57.208
[muffled grunting]

1027
01:18:04.250 --> 01:18:06.250
[gasps. breathing heavily]

1028
01:18:15.458 --> 01:18:16.916
[Hutt sister laughs]

1029
01:18:17.458 --> 01:18:19.916
[laughing]

1030
01:18:22.041 --> 01:18:24.041
[water stirs]

1031
01:18:31.666 --> 01:18:34.041
[♪ Tense music playing]

1032
01:18:50.458 --> 01:18:51.458
[grunts]

1033
01:18:54.583 --> 01:18:55.666
[coughing. gasping]

1034
01:19:00.083 --> 01:19:01.833
[grunting]

1035
01:19:03.083 --> 01:19:04.083
[grunts. gasps]

1036
01:19:04.791 --> 01:19:06.291
[hisses]

1037
01:19:08.500 --> 01:19:10.458
[grunts. strains]

1038
01:19:14.458 --> 01:19:16.250
[♪ Music stops]

1039
01:19:22.291 --> 01:19:24.250
[♪ Tense music plays]

1040
01:19:38.166 --> 01:19:39.791
[breathes shakily]

1041
01:19:44.833 --> 01:19:47.291
- [roars]
- [grunting]

1042
01:19:49.500 --> 01:19:50.500
[grunts]

1043
01:19:51.125 --> 01:19:52.625
[grunting]

1044
01:19:57.125 --> 01:19:58.791
[♪ Dramatic music plays]

1045
01:20:00.708 --> 01:20:02.416
- [growling]
- [grunts]

1046
01:20:03.833 --> 01:20:05.416
- [grunting]
- [screeches]

1047
01:20:05.500 --> 01:20:07.625
[straining. grunts]

1048
01:20:07.708 --> 01:20:09.333
- [shouts]
- [roars]

1049
01:20:10.291 --> 01:20:11.500
[grunts]

1050
01:20:11.583 --> 01:20:14.791
[growling. groans]

1051
01:20:15.958 --> 01:20:17.708
[groans]

1052
01:20:27.291 --> 01:20:29.875
[Hutt brother. in Huttese] You have entertained us.

1053
01:20:30.666 --> 01:20:32.916
Here is your reward.

1054
01:20:34.708 --> 01:20:36.208
[helmet clanging]

1055
01:20:43.500 --> 01:20:44.583
[water sloshing]

1056
01:20:52.916 --> 01:20:55.708
- [hissing]
- [♪ dramatic music plays]

1057
01:21:16.208 --> 01:21:17.625
[inhales sharply]

1058
01:21:23.791 --> 01:21:25.125
[roaring]

1059
01:21:30.125 --> 01:21:31.125
[grunts]

1060
01:21:34.958 --> 01:21:36.041
[grunts]

1061
01:21:37.750 --> 01:21:38.750
[grunts]

1062
01:21:39.291 --> 01:21:40.500
- [growls]
- [grunts]

1063
01:21:42.166 --> 01:21:43.833
[breathes heavily]

1064
01:21:45.333 --> 01:21:46.458
[grunts]

1065
01:21:46.541 --> 01:21:48.125
[muffled grunting]

1066
01:21:54.291 --> 01:21:55.291
[gasps]

1067
01:21:57.333 --> 01:21:58.583
- [roars]
- [grunts]

